  <prompt>
    Replace the hardcoded GUID at `WorkspaceAiService.cs:41-44` with a stable-code lookup via `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync(WorkspaceOptions.AiSummaryPlaybookCode, tenantId)`. Confirm the target stable code value (deferred decision in task 013 — likely `summarize-new-files` or `document-profile`); update `WorkspaceOptions.AiSummaryPlaybookCode` default + appsettings if needed. Pattern A migration shape.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in workspace AI summarization layer + Pattern A migrations.</role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceAiService.cs` resolves the summary playbook via `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync(options.AiSummaryPlaybookCode, tenantId)`. Hardcoded GUID removed. The `AiSummaryPlaybookCode` value populated in `appsettings.Development.json` matches the intended production playbook (decision documented in handoff). Unit + integration tests pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-02 + §1.7 Pattern A. `WorkspaceAiService.cs:41-44` carries a hardcoded GUID for the workspace-side AI summary playbook. Spec §1.7.3 codes table includes `summarize-new-files` and `document-profile`; the deferred-decision item in task 013 leaves the exact target for resolution here. Trace the GUID at `:41-44` to its production playbook via Dataverse `read_query` to confirm which code to bind.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/WorkspaceAiService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/WorkspaceOptions.cs (read-only — set in task 013; may need value-only update)</file>
      <file>config/appsettings.Development.json (value-only update if AiSummaryPlaybookCode default was empty)</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/WorkspaceAiServiceTests.cs</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/WorkspaceAiIntegrationTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Inject `IOptions&lt;WorkspaceOptions&gt;` + `IPlaybookLookupService` directly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service inside `Services/Ai/` — consumer crosses AI facade; preserve public contract.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Cached lookup.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Typed options.</constraint>
